<HEADLINE> Clinton To Attend Chafee Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will attend a memorial  
service for Sen. John Chafee, who died Sunday evening of heart 
failure at Bethesda Naval Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The White House announced today that Clinton will travel to  
Rhode Island on Saturday for the service. 
</P>
<P>
	The president lauded Chafee, a Republican, as a lawmaker who  
``embodied the decent center which has carried America from triumph 
to triumph for over 200 years.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
