<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Men Charged in Tenn. Arson Spree </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Two men were arrested on charges of  
tossing matches out of their car and igniting 100 brush fires 
across four counties in central Tennessee. 
</P>
<P>
	Lester Clouse, 36, and Michael Carter, 18, were charged with  
arson for flicking the matches Tuesday, said Sheriff Jerry Abston. 
Clouse threatened deputies with a knife and also was charged with 
assault and resisting arrest, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	``They were just driving the roads and I guess they were having  
a good time,'' Abston said. 
</P>
<P>
	A smoky haze lingered Wednesday after authorities snuffed out  
the last of the fires. Damage was limited to woodlands and 
grasslands as firefighters kept flames away from homes or barns. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been doing this kind of work for 15 years and I've never  
seen anything like it,'' said Fire Chief Daryl Blair. ``Some of the 
fires were the size of a football; others were two or three times 
the size of a football field.'' 
</P>
<P>
	About 300 citizens helped 100 mostly volunteer firefighters  
tackle the blazes in Smith, DeKalb, Putnam and White counties. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
