<HEADLINE> Ex-Virginia Prison Guard Indicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- A former guard at Virginia's largest prison  
for women has been indicted on a charge of exposing himself to an 
inmate. 
</P>
<P>
	The charge of indecent exposure against Richard Keith Robinson  
is a misdemeanor that carries a maximum penalty of a year in jail 
or a $2,500 fine, or both. Robinson, who was fired by the Fluvanna 
Correctional Center for Women, will appear in court Nov. 12, and a 
trial date may be set then. 
</P>
<P>
	Commonwealth's Attorney Colin Guy said he received two other  
cases from the prison on Tuesday in which inmates allege sexual 
battery by guards. He said he has not determined whether he will 
prosecute the cases. 
</P>
<P>
	The Associated Press reported Oct. 11 that there had been nearly  
a threefold increase in such complaints this year. 
  	   	
</P>
