<HEADLINE> AP Corrects U.N.-Buchanan Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNITED NATIONS (AP) -- The Associated Press, in an Oct. 26 story  
about U.N. reaction to comments made by presidential candidate Pat 
Buchanan, erroneously quoted U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard as saying 
the issue of the United States possibly losing its U.N. vote was 
related to Article 13 of the U.N. Charter. 
</P>
<P>
	Eckhard said the issue related to Article 19, not 13.  
  	   	
