<HEADLINE> Brunell, Taylor Probable for Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Jaguars quarterback Mark Brunell and  
running back Fred Taylor are both listed as probable for Sunday's 
game at Cincinnati. 
</P>
<P>
	Brunell has a strained muscle near his ribs that he aggravated  
two weeks ago while throwing a long pass against Cleveland. Taylor 
has been out since Oct. 3 with an aggravated hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	Brunell threw less than usual in practice Wednesday. He said he  
needs to know he can make all the throws if he's to start. 
</P>
<P>
	``But you don't make them all now,'' Brunell said. ``You make  
them as you get closer to the game. The long ball is certainly 
something I've got to be able to throw Sunday.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Taylor's injury has progressed steadily since he left in the  
middle of a game against the Steelers. Coach Tom Coughlin said some 
of Jacksonville's troubles on offense might be solved with Taylor 
back in the lineup. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully he'll be ready to perform this weekend,'' Coughlin  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Coughlin said backup quarterback Jay Fiedler would get more  
repetitions than usual in practice this week. He said a final 
decision on Brunell's status would be made later in the week. 
  	   	
