<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Skies were mostly clear Wednesday around the United States, with  
low clouds keeping temperatures cool in the Northeast and scattered 
rain along the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	Clear conditions prevailed from the Great Lakes and Ohio Valley  
south through the Mississippi Valley and east to the mid-Atlantic 
and Southeast. 
</P>
<P>
	Parts of Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont and New York state had  
temperatures in the 30s and 40s, aided by cloud cover. A cold front 
was pushing into the northern Plains, bringing some clouds and rain 
to parts of the Dakotas. 
</P>
<P>
	Skies were also partly cloudy from southern Colorado and western  
Kansas, south into New Mexico and western Texas. Light rain was 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Rain was scattered along the West Coast, from Washington to  
northern California. Wind gusted to 35 mph in Troutdale, Ore., and 
Renton, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the lower 48 states was 91 degrees in  
College Station, Texas. The low was 16 degree in Craig, Colo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
