<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Education Dept. Findings on Y2K </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some findings from the Education Department's Y2K report:  
</P>
<P>
	Among schools for kindergarten through 12th grade:  
</P>
<P>
	--65 percent had completed contingency planning, and 83 percent  
declared they would have them in place by Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	--73 percent said all central administrative systems such as  
accounting, finance and payroll were Y2K-compliant, and 96 percent 
declared administrative systems would be by Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	--72 percent said all student services such as student records,  
bus schedules and cafeteria operations were compliant, and 96 
percent declared they would be by the start of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	--56 percent said all infrastructure such as heating, security  
and telecommunications systems were compliant, and 86 percent 
declared they would be by Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	------	 
</P>
<P>
	Among colleges, universities and trade schools:  
</P>
<P>
	--73 percent had completed contingency planning, and 88 percent  
declared they would have them in place by the first of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	--67 percent said central administrative systems were compliant,  
and 95 percent declared they would be by Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	--70 percent said student services were complaint, and 96 percent  
declared they would be by Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	--Just 62 percent said infrastructure components were compliant,  
and 85 percent declared they would be by Jan. 1. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
