<HEADLINE> German Pop Singer Rex Gildo Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MUNICH, Germany (AP) -- German pop singer Rex Gildo died of heart  
failure three days after attempting suicide by jumping from his 
third-floor apartment window, a Munich hospital spokeswoman said. 
He was 60. 
</P>
<P>
	Gildo died Tuesday night after three days in an artificially  
induced coma, the spokeswoman said. She spoke on condition of 
anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Gildo had been suffering from psychological  
problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Gildo, whose real name was Ludwig Hirtreiter, rode to fame in  
the 1960s and '70s with hits like ``Fiesta Mexicana'' and ``Speedy 
Gonzales.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He continued to perform in recent years at events like folk  
festivals. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
