<HEADLINE> Okla. Cop Accused of Sexual Battery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) -- A police officer being investigated in  
connection with the alleged rape of a bartender at a police social 
club was charged with sexual battery Wednesday in a separate 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
	Capt. Bill Martin was accused of groping a female security guard  
and making suggestive comments on Sept. 5 near the police station 
he oversaw. 
</P>
<P>
	The charge carries a maximum sentence of five years in prison.  
</P>
<P>
	Martin also is the focus of an investigation into events that  
occurred at a police social club called the Glitter Dome on Sept. 
25. A bartender says she was raped by one or more officers. 
</P>
<P>
	Police have released a 911 call that Martin placed from the club  
saying the woman was drunk and nude. Martin also said he saw three 
or four condoms, but police responding to the club said they didn't 
find any. 
</P>
<P>
	Martin is out of state and has been on personal leave since the  
investigation began. Martin's attorney said he would talk to Martin 
on Wednesday night by telephone and promised that the officer would 
be back in Oklahoma City by Friday for arraignment. 
  	   	
</P>
