<HEADLINE> Champions League Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Defending champion Manchester United beat Croatia Zagreb 2-1  
Wednesday to reach the round of 16 of the Champions League. 
</P>
<P>
	Four other teams also advanced: Lazio and Fiorentina of Italy,  
Rosenborg of Norway and Olympique Marseille of France. 
</P>
<P>
	The five join six other clubs that already have qualified:  
Barcelona, Real Madrid, Valencia of Spain, Bordeaux of France, 
Porto of Portugal and Sparta Prague of the Czech Republic. Five 
spots are to be decided next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United got goals from David Beckham and Roy Keane to  
hold off the Croatians and move on from Group D. Olympique 
Marseille got the other berth despite a 3-2 loss at Sturm Graz. The 
Austrians had scored only one goal in their previous four games. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazio won Group A with a 1-1 tie at home over Bayer Leverkusen.  
In the other group match, last year's semifinalist Dynamo Kiev won 
2-1 at Maribor. Dynamo can claim the other place by beating Lazio 
in Kiev next week. Leverkusen faces Maribor and needs a Dynamo loss 
to have a chance. 
</P>
<P>
	Fiorentina got a 75th-minute goal from Gabriel Batistuta to beat  
Arsenal 1-0 at Wembley in Group B and eliminate the English. 
Barcelona routed AIK Solna 5-0 in the other group game on two goals 
from Patrick Kluivert. 
</P>
<P>
	Rosenborg beat Portugal's Boavista 2-0 to advance from Group C  
with 11 points. Borussia Dortmund and Feyenoord tied 1-1. Borussia 
has six points and can win a place by beating Boavista next week. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
