<HEADLINE> Brock Selected as LA Avengers Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Stan Brock, who played in the NFL for 16  
years, will be the first head coach of the Arena Football League's 
Los Angeles Avengers. 
</P>
<P>
	The 41-year-old Brock was introduced at a news conference  
Tuesday at the Staples Center, where the Avengers will play their 
home games in their inaugural season, which begins next April. 
</P>
<P>
	Brock grew up in Portland, Ore., and was a four-year letterman  
at Colorado. He then played offensive tackle for the New Orleans 
Saints for 13 years and the San Diego Chargers for three before 
retiring in 1995 after playing 234 games in the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
	Brock coached the Portland Forest Dragons of the Arena League  
for the past 2 1/2 seasons. Portland was 7-7 last year, and was 12-24 
under Brock, who took the job after Don Frease resigned in June 
1997, before the team's seventh game. 
</P>
<P>
	Brock signed a three-year contract with the Avengers as coach  
and director of football operations. Terms were not announced. 
</P>
<P>
	``In the past three years, I've become addicted to coaching, and  
this is such a tremendous opportunity,'' Brock said. ``The 
challenge of building the foundation of this franchise is something 
that I'm really looking forward to.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
