<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NAACP Eyes Sanctions Against Tigers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- The NAACP accused the Detroit Tigers of ignoring  
baseball's initiative to consider minorities for management 
positions and is asking the sport's commissioner to impose economic 
sanctions. 
</P>
<P>
	Standing in front of Comerica Park, the new home for the Detroit  
Tigers, NAACP president Kwesi Mfume said the Tigers' refusal to 
comply with the diversity initiative is ``essentially a slap in the 
face'' to minority coaches. 
</P>
<P>
	At issue is the Tigers' decision to hire Phil Garner, who is  
white, as manager for the Detroit Tigers. Garner is not the 
problem, Tigers owner Mike Ilitch is, Mfume said. 
</P>
<P>
	After Garner's hire was announced Oct. 14, Commissioner Bud  
Selig issued a statement saying he is conducting a review of the 
hiring of Garner to see if the team complied with the league's 
minority-hiring initiative. 
</P>
<P>
	``We call on Mr. Ilitch to publicly apologize for this egregious  
affront to African-Americans and Latino communities all over this 
nation who believe in baseball, who love this sport and who believe 
in equal opportunity,'' Mfume said. 
</P>
<P>
	When asked what type of sanctions he wanted baseball to impose  
on the team, Mfume wouldn't elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	Tigers spokesman Tyler Barnes declined to say whether any  
minorities had been interviewed for the manager position because of 
the commissioner's ongoing investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	But he defended the team's commitment to diversity, touting the  
$60 million in construction contracts that has been awarded to 
minority firms to build Comerica Park. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is no organization that is more committed to equal  
opportunity employment and the inclusion of minority business 
communities than the Tigers,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mfume called for the Detroit minority community to send a  
message to Ilitch by not spending money at his places of business. 
In addition to owning the Tigers, Ilitch owns Little Caesar's 
pizza, the Rockers soccer team, the Fox Theatre and several 
restaurants. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
