<HEADLINE> Results From New Presidential Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some results from poll questions released Wednesday on the 2000  
presidential race. When results don't total 100 percent, the 
remainder either didn't know or refused to answer. 

</P>
<P>
	If the election for president were held today whom would you  
support if the candidates are Al Gore, the Democrat, and George W. 
Bush, the Republican? 
</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 53 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Gore, 39 percent (Marist)  

</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 49 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Gore, 39 percent (NBC/WSJ)  

</P>
<P>
	If the election for president were held today, whom would you  
support if the candidates were Bill Bradley, the Democrat, and 
George W. Bush, the Republican? 
</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 52 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Bradley, 37 percent (Marist)  

</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 43 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Bradley, 38 percent (NBC/WSJ)  

</P>
<P>
	If the election for president were held today, whom would you  
support if the candidates are George W. Bush, Al Gore and Pat 
Buchanan? 
</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 49 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Gore, 36 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Buchanan, 6 percent (Marist)  

</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 44 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Gore, 38 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Buchanan, 6 percent (NBC/WSJ)  

</P>
<P>
	If the election for president were held today, whom would you  
support if the candidates are George W. Bush, Bill Bradley, Pat 
Buchanan? 
</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 49 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Bradley, 35 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Buchanan, 6 percent (Marist)  

</P>
<P>
	--Bush, 43 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Bradley, 38 percent  
</P>
<P>
	--Buchanan, 8 percent (NBC/WSJ)  

</P>
<P>
	The NBC/WSJ questions were asked of all adults in the poll,  
while the Marist questions were asked of registered voters. 

</P>
<P>
	The Marist telephone poll of 1,013 adults, including 761  
registered voters, was taken Oct. 18-20 and has an error margin of 
plus or minus 3 percentage points, larger for subgroups like 
registered voters. The NBC/Wall Street Journal poll of 1,003 adults 
was taken Oct. 23-25 and has an error margin of plus or minus 3 
percentage points. 
  	   	
</P>
