<HEADLINE> Dodgers To Name New Chairman, CEO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Los Angeles Dodgers on Thursday will name  
a new chairman and chief executive officer who is purchasing a 
small part of the team, a source close to the team said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dodgers would only say a ``major executive appointment'' is  
planned for 10 a.m. PDT at the Staples Center. 
</P>
<P>
	The source, who spoke on condition of anonymity, told The  
Associated Press on Wednesday the new chairman and CEO will be ``a 
famous entertainment person who lives in Los Angeles.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The source wouldn't provide further details.  
</P>
<P>
	Bob Graziano was fired as president and CEO of the Dodgers late  
last month -- shortly before the team finished a most disappointing 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Graziano, 41, joined the Dodgers in January 1986, and became  
president and CEO when the Fox Group division of Rupert Murdoch's 
News Corp. bought the team from Peter O'Malley's family on March 
19, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dodgers have been underachievers since the sale to Fox. Last  
year, they finished 83-79 and in third place in the NL West. This 
year, as prohibitive favorites in the division with a $79.2 million 
opening-day payroll -- second highest in the majors -- they wound up 
77-85 and 23 games behind first-place Arizona. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
