<HEADLINE> Daiei Hawks Lead Japan Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAGOYA, Japan (AP) -- Hiroki Kokubo drove in two runs and Junji  
Hoshino allowed three hits in 6 1/3 innings as the Daiei Hawks 
defeated the Chunichi Dragons 3-0 Wednesday, moving within one 
victory of winning their first Japan Series championship. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hawks, who won the Pacific League pennant for the first time  
in the team's 11-year history, lead the best-of-7 series 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
	They could end the series in Game 5 Thursday at the Nagoya Dome,  
home of the Central League champion Dragons. 
</P>
<P>
	Koji Akiyama doubled home the first run after an infield hit by  
Chihiro Hamana and Kokubo singled home the second run in the third 
inning for the Hawks. In the sixth, Kokubo hit his first homer of 
the series. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoshino was relieved by Takayuki Shinohara in the seventh. In  
the bottom of the ninth, reliever Rodney Pedraza got Leo Gomez to 
ground into a game-ending double play for his first save of the 
series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
