<HEADLINE> Report: Dan Marino Out 2-3 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Miami Dolphins quarterback Dan Marino will  
miss 2-3 weeks because of a flareup of a disc in his neck, 
according to a broadcast report. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox Sports News, citing unidentified Dolphins sources, said  
Marino's malady was triggered by the bone spur in his lower neck 
which has idled him for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	Marino was in Los Angeles to meet with Dr. Robert Watkins for a  
second opinion on his condition. Watkins has operated on the backs 
of quarterbacks Troy Aikman, Joe Montana and, more recently, Steve 
McNair. 
</P>
<P>
	According to Fox, no surgery is required but Marino will be out  
until at least Nov. 14, when Miami plays Buffalo. 
</P>
<P>
	With Marino unable to throw effectively, Damon Huard has been  
starting at quarterback for Miami. 
  	   	
</P>
