``The Wild Party,'' a musical opening next year on Broadway. The 
show is based on the Jazz Age poem by Joseph Moncure March. 
Collette's films include ``The Sixth Sense,'' ``Velvet Goldmine'' 
and ``Muriel's Wedding.'' When she isn't working, she goes on 
retreats in India, climbs mountains in Tibet and practices yoga. 
``I want to study holistic medicine. Basically I see myself in a 
rain forest with long, white dreadlocks working with herbs,'' says 
Collette, who was born on Nov. 1, 1972. 

