<HEADLINE> Yen Up Vs. Dollar; Euro, Pound Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The yen continued its upward march against the  
dollar Wednesday on expectations that Japan will spend significant 
amounts of money to shore up its economy. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the dollar fell to 104.17 Japanese yen  
from 104.69 yen late Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Japanese currency has been gaining ground against the dollar  
in recent trading sessions on expectations that the next government 
spending plan will be bigger than earlier projected. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro fell slightly against the dollar despite growing  
expectations that the European Central Bank will raise interest 
rates when it meets next week. The common currency for 11 European 
nations was quoted at $1.0500, down from $1.0586 late Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.5244 Swiss francs, up from  
1.5122, and 1.4721 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4744. The British 
pound fell to $1.6439 from $1.6532. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the European countries participating in the euro  
are no longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed 
rate. Based on Wednesday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8633 
German marks, up from 1.8481; 6.2491 French francs, up from 6.1982; 
and 1,844.42 Italian lire, up from 1,829.60. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
