<HEADLINE> Colorado Gov. Makes Ramsey Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Gov. Bill Owens said Wednesday he has decided not  
to appoint a special prosecutor to look into the JonBenet Ramsey 
slaying, saying police are working with new evidence and headed in 
the right direction. 
</P>
<P>
	Owens also asked the little girl's parents, John and Patsy  
Ramsey, to ``stop hiding behind their attorneys'' and return to 
Colorado to help authorities track down their daughter's killers. 
  	   	
