<HEADLINE> Broadway Producer to Wed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- David Merrick, producer of Broadway hits  
including ``Hello Dolly'' and ``42nd Street,'' is planning to marry 
his longtime companion, Natalie Ting Lloyd. 
</P>
<P>
	Merrick's lawyer said he expects Merrick, 88, and the  
Shanghai-born Ms. Lloyd, 45, to marry ``quite soon.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The plan was disclosed last week when Merrick asked that a  
judgment be entered in the divorce case filed by Etan Merrick, who 
was his third and fifth wife. 
</P>
<P>
	She was granted a divorce four years ago on grounds of  
abandonment, but the judgment was never entered. Mrs. Merrick 
opposed entry of the judgment before financial issues like alimony 
and child support were settled. 
</P>
<P>
	Merrick's fortune is estimated at $14 million.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
