<HEADLINE> Panthers 6, Islanders 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SUNRISE, Fla. (AP) -- Pavel Bure scored two goals in his first  
action in two weeks as the Florida Panthers defeated the New York 
Islanders 6-3 Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Bure and Mark Parrish each scored twice as the Panthers snapped  
a two-game losing streak. The six goals were the most by Florida 
this season. 
</P>
