<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold was also mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0533 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0584 Tuesday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the 
euro traded at $1.0540. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Tuesday,  
included 104.20 Japanese yen, down from 104.89; 1.5182 Swiss 
francs, up from 1.5110; 1.4704 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4714. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6474, down from $1.6533.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 103.83 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6488. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8569 German marks, up from 1.8476; 
6.2294 French francs, up from 6.1959; 2.0924 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0815; 1839.16 Italian lire, up from 1,829.09. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $291.30 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$289.40 on Tuesday. In Zurich the bid price was $291.70, up from 
$289.00. Gold fell $6.88 in Hong Kong to close at $291.38. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.19 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.22. 
  	   	
</P>
