<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Grizzlies' Long To Miss 4-6 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- Veteran forward Grant Long,  
one of Vancouver's key offseason acquisitions, will miss four to 
six weeks with a sprained left knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Long, an 11-year veteran, was hurt in a three-player collision  
during Tuesday's 105-97 win over Denver. It was Long's first game 
back after missing four games with a concussion. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury is a big blow to the Grizzlies, who signed the  
free-agent power forward to bolster their frontcourt depth last 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's just a tough loss for us,'' coach Brian Hill said  
Wednesday. ``We just got the guy back and bang, another injury 
happens right away. ... It was obvious what type of impact Grant 
was making on our team prior to his injury with his leadership and 
his communication. It was rubbing off on everybody and we miss that 
out there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Long hopes to be back by the end of November.  
</P>
<P>
	``It is frustrating,'' he said. ``Luckily it's still the  
preseason. We don't get under way for another week, and I'm still 
counting that week as a week into my rehab. I look at it as a 
three-to-four week deal as opposed to five or six. Hopefully some 
good things will happen with some good rehab.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Long is the latest in a long line of hobbled Grizzlies. The  
injured include center Bryant Reeves (sore knee), Othella 
Harrington (bruised ankle), Doug West (toe surgery) and Antoine 
Carr (sore knee). 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
