<HEADLINE> Arizona Executes Man for '78 Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FLORENCE, Ariz. (AP) -- A man who fatally stabbed his ex-lover,  
tried to kill her children and then set the woman's body on fire 
was executed by injection Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ignacio Alberto Ortiz, 57, was convicted of the 1978 murder of  
Manuelita McCormack at her Tucson home. He also was convicted of 
attempting to kill her three young children that night to eliminate 
witnesses and of later plotting to have them killed by a jail 
cellmate. 
</P>
<P>
	According to trial testimony, Ortiz had been romantically  
involved with Mrs. McCormack while she was estranged from her 
husband. Mrs. McCormack was killed after she reconciled with her 
husband and told Ortiz she did not want to see him anymore. 
</P>
<P>
	Ortiz fatally stabbed Mrs. McCormack and then attacked the  
children. The children fled the house after Ortiz poured gasoline 
on and around their mother's body and set it afire. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
